    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-02-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-02-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="473" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d473">
                <head>No. 474.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Peixotto</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Hunter</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Consulate of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Bucharest</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-02-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 6, 1872</date>. (Received March
                                    5,)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 18.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to inform you that accounts
                                have reached here of deplorable scenes which have recently
                                transpired in several towns of Bessarabian Roumania, and especially
                                at Ismail, Vilcovu, and Cabool.</p>
                <p>The population had rushed upon the Israelites, devastated their
                                homes, and blood had been shed.</p>
                <p>Hundreds of families had been beaten, despoiled, and driven
                                forth.</p>
                <p>Hundreds had fled across the Danube for refuge in Turkey.</p>
                <p>* * * * * * *</p>
                <p>I am, sir, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>BENJ. F. PEIXOTTO,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">United States
                                        Consul.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
